        "comment": "Element `ChargeItem.product` allows multiple values in the source, but is mapped to an element that does not allow multiple values in the target.\nElement `ChargeItem.product` is mapped to FHIR R4 element `ChargeItem.product[x]` as `SourceIsBroaderThanTarget`.\nThe mappings for `ChargeItem.product` do not cover the following types: CodeableReference.\nThe target context `ChargeItem.product[x]` is a choice-type element and cannot directly hold extensions. The context is moved up to parent element `ChargeItem`.",
